How can I extract the subject, verb, and object from a given sentence using the Stanford CoreNLP library in Java? For example, if I have the sentence "John ate an apple," how can I use CoreNLP to extract "John" as the subject, "ate" as the verb, and "an apple" as the object?
Here is an example Java code using the Stanford CoreNLP library to achieve this:
import java.util.*;
import edu.stanford.nlp.pipeline.*;
import edu.stanford.nlp.ling.*;
import edu.stanford.nlp.semgraph.*;
import edu.stanford.nlp.util.*;
import edu.stanford.nlp.simple.*;
public class SentenceParser {
  public static void main(String[] args) {
    // Set up the pipeline
    Properties props = new Properties();
    props.setProperty("annotators", "tokenize, ssplit, pos, lemma, parse, depparse");
    StanfordCoreNLP pipeline = new StanfordCoreNLP(props);
    // Define the sentence to be parsed
    String sentence = "John ate an apple.";
    // Parse the sentence
    CoreDocument document = new CoreDocument(sentence);
    pipeline.annotate(document);
    // Extract the subject, verb, and object
    List<CoreLabel> tokens = document.tokens();
    for (CoreLabel token : tokens) {
      String word = token.word();
      String pos = token.get(CoreAnnotations.PartOfSpeechAnnotation.class);
      if (pos.startsWith("V")) {
        System.out.println("Verb: " + word);
      } else if (pos.startsWith("N")) {
        System.out.println("Subject/Object: " + word);
      }
    }
  }
}
This code uses the Stanford CoreNLP library to tokenize, split, tag, lemmatize, parse, and deparse the input sentence, and then iterates through the resulting list of tokens to identify the verb and the subject/object.

